reviewText: I indicated in one of my previous reviews that it was very unfortunate that in this age of CD/video many true legendary "soul" artist who's music had transended generations from the 1970s to the 1990s had remained largely ignored by the industry in favor of "popcorn" "flash in the pan" acts like "Lady Gaga" who no one will remember 5 years from now.  These legends include Al Green, Peabo Bryson, Gerald Alston(Mahattans), Barry White, and the O'Jays.  Although Barry White at least has one DVD concert (Live in Germany), its perhaps the worst performance of his stellar carrier!  So, it is great to hear that finally an O'Jays concert is coming to DVD!  I am sure many fans will be anxious to finally have a live concert of these legends, who despite having a carrier lasting over 3 decades don't have a single concert on DVD!  I can't give true star review without seeing the concert, but if the performace is one of their best, it should get at least 4 stars and will give their millions of fans a true treasure to remember them by.  Lets keep our fingers crossed, but first we need the song listing before we buy! Now, if only the same could be done for the other great artists too!

reviewText: What a way to celebrate 50 or more years in music! In style! I bought this DVD on bluray and it is beautiful. Though the stage for me seems too small the O'Jays - Eddie, Walter and Eric and the band are just great. Forever Mine, Use Ta Be My Girl, For the Love of Money, Stairway to Heaven - all great performances. I am dissapointed though that they instead played a very short version of You've Got Your Hooks in Me. To the O'Jays and Group Management release more...Brandy, Ship Ahoy, a longer You've Got Your Hooks in Me, You Won't Fail, Your Body is Here with Me...you get the drift.

reviewText: As a frequent Amazon buyer from Europe, I'm always searching for special performances dvds, and I may say that this is one of them. The grace and the ease with which Walter en Eddie still do their stuff, is nothing less than amazing. Got on track for this dvd through Three Degree Valerie Holiday, when they were in Europe. I complimented her on their performace on the Sound of Philadelphia DVD. Then she said, the O'Jays made another dvd, just their own concert. Bought it without hesitation and it's great from beginning to end! Must have! Enjoy!
